data.title: iLead Neighborhood Leadership Training
data.meta_description: iLead is a comprehensive program that provides neighborhood organizations with the tools to inform, connect and involve your neighbors through a series of guides and trainings.
data.text:
iLead workshops include customized training at association meetings, monthly community connection workshops and the annual Neighborhood and Community Summit.

Community Connections Workshops

Community Connection Workshops are free workshops usually held on the 2nd Saturday of the month, designed to inform, connect and involve citizens with a variety of topics. They are also a great opportunity for neighborhood leaders to interact and learn from one another.

View upcoming workshops

Neighborhood Association Customized Training

Ongoing by request. Contact our office at 407.246.2169.

Neighborhoods U.S.A.

Neighborhoods U.S.A. (NUSA) is an annual conference that provides an opportunity for people from various communities throughout the United States to discuss the pressing issues of the time, share the best practices and offer encouragement and assistance.

The City of Orlando is the owner of the mark “iLead” in connection with the programs outlined on this site. The City of Orlando is happy for other local governments to use the materials found on this site as long as 1) credit is given to the City of Orlando if such materials are re-used by another local government and 2) no commercial use is made of the materials.
